9. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188646" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ocodoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ocodoma diffusa" lsidName-HNS="Ocodoma Diffusa Jerdon" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffusa">Ocodoma diffusa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel>N. S.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="109">Worker about 1 / 8 th of an inch long; head somewhat oval, nearly smooth, with a few scattered graundes, slightly emarginate behind; eyes moderate size; thorax deeply grooved, with two small spines pos-teriorly: first abdominal pedicle very pointed, conic; second rounded of equal height: head, thorax and legs rufous; abdomen brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="109">Warrior 1 / 4 th inch long, jaw strongly toothed, head large, much striated, deeply notched behind; thorax more deeply grooved and tubercled; otherwise as in the Worker. This species appears to be spread over most of India, and has similar habits to the last.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
